Sirisia MP John Waluke has said he will run for Bungoma governor in 2022, when &ldquo;incumbent Kenneth Lusaka completes his second term.&rdquo;He said on Friday he will sustain Lusaka&rsquo;s &ldquo;sterling performance&rdquo;. Waluke was addressing Bungoma town residents during a JP rally in Posta Grounds.He urged voters to reelect Lusaka to complete the projects he has started, saying he is the best thing that ever happened to the county.&lsquo;&rsquo;Those with eyes can see that Bungoma has really transformed in the past four years . Roads have been built, schools have been refurbished, youths and women have been empowered and stalled factories have been relaunched. We want him to continue with that.&rdquo;